-- Chile Convenes Emergency Meeting on Europe Crisis, Mercurio Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2012-05-25T13:10:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/chile-convenes-emergency-meeting-on-europe-crisis-mercurio-says.html
Chilean President Sebastian Pinera
convened an emergency meeting for next week to prepare for a
potential deepening of the European economic crisis, El Mercurio
 reported today , citing Labor Minister Evelyn Matthei and Economy
Minister Pablo Longueira.  The government may increase spending as part of a
contingency plan designed to protect employment, investment and
liquidity if the European crisis slows growth in the Andean
nation, the  Santiago-based newspaper  reported, citing government
sources it didnâ€™t name.  To contact the reporter on this story:
